<TITLE> Banks remain open Saturday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 26 (bdnews24.com) All banks will remain open Saturday to provide an extra banking day for customers. The extra day was particularly meant for potential taxpayers to take advantage of the National Board of Revenue's facility to legalise undeclared income. SundaySept 30is the extended deadline for legalising untaxed money under NBR's initiative to allow the public to pay an extra 5 percent tax penalty on untaxed money. Following a request by the NBR, the central bank issued a circular to all the retail banks directing them to keep their offices open Saturday, Sep 29. "In the interest of revenue collections, all branches of scheduled banks will remain open according to work schedule by ensuring adequate security arrangement," the central bank said in a statement. bdnews24.c
